    All Classes and Interfaces

    Classes
    Class
    Description
    App
    Main application entry point.
    AreaButtonHandler
    Handles the action of the "Area" button click.
    ButtonHandlerFactory
    A factory class to create appropriate ActionListeners for different button actions.
    CsvToPropertyReader
    The CsvToPropertyReader class is responsible for: - Reading property data from a CSV file
    DetailsButtonHandler
    Handles the action of the "Details" button click.
    ExtraButtonHandler
    Handles the action of the "Extra" button click.
    MadeiraMapGUI
    The MadeiraMapGUI class represents the main graphical user interface (GUI) for the Madeira Property Map system.
    OwnerGraphButtonHandler
    Handles the action when the "Owner Graph" button is clicked.
    Property
    Represents a property with various attributes such as object ID, parcel details, geometry, owner information, and location details (freguesia, municipio, ilha).
    PropertyAdjacencyUtils
    Utility class for handling property adjacencies.
    PropertyGeometryPlotter
    Class for visualizing property geometries on XY charts.
    PropertyGeometryUtils
    Utility class for handling geometric operations related to properties.
    PropertyGraph
    The PropertyGraph class is responsible for creating and visualizing a graph of properties.
    PropertyManager
    Utility class to manage property-related operations.
    PropertyMapButtonHandler
    Handles the action when the "Property Map" button is clicked.
    PropertyMergeUtils
    Utility class for merging adjacent properties with the same owner.
    PropertySwapManager
    Utility class to handle property swap suggestions.
    PropertySwapSuggestion
    The PropertySwapSuggestion class represents a suggestion for swapping two properties between different owners.
    PropertySwapSuggestionPrinter
    Utility class to handle printing of property swap suggestions and related metrics.
    SuggestionButtonHandler
    Handles the action when the "Suggestion" button is clicked.
